description: From Latin suscitatus, past participle of suscitare (“to lift up, to rouse”), from sub- + citare (“to rouse, excite”). Compare excite, incite, and resuscitate.

verbs.description: suscitate (third-person singular simple present suscitates, present participle suscitating, simple past and past participle suscitated)

entries.meaning: (obsolete, transitive) To rouse; to excite; to call into life and action.
